    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "okay so basically i'm the one paying if they get sued? that seems pretty risky for a freelancer. like if i use a font that i thought was fine but turns out it's not, i'd have to pay for their legal fees too?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "That's the right way to look at the core of it, yes, you're essentially agreeing to cover the costs if the other side gets into a mess. A proper indemnification clause can be a real tripwire, like a poorly placed tripwire in a dark cave. You're right to be cautious about that font example; if that font causes a lawsuit, the contract says *you* have to pay their legal fees. It's a big chunk of your personal, or at least your business's, potential risk.",
